<!-- ABOUT SECTION -->
<section class="about-box">

    <h2>About IIBSE</h2>

    <p>
        Indian International Board of Skills Schools & Education (IIBSE) is an autonomous 
        national-level skill education and examination board established to promote modern skill 
        development, professional training, academic enhancement, and competency-based learning 
        for students, institutions, and trainers across India and abroad.
    </p>

    <p>
        IIBSE provides affiliation to schools, training centres, institutions, academies, skill hubs, and 
        vocational centres to implement national-level competency standards, digital education systems,
        modern curriculum frameworks, and student certification.
    </p>

    <p>
        The Board offers digital learning support, online and offline examination frameworks, 
        vocational assessment, professional registration of certified candidates, and 
        verification services for employers and organizations.
    </p>

    <div class="heading">Our Purpose</div>
    <p>
        IIBSE aims to develop a quality ecosystem for skill-based learning from school level to 
        advanced professional levels. The purpose is to support the nation’s vision of Skill India, 
        Digital India, and global workforce development by empowering students with employable skills.
    </p>

    <div class="heading">What We Do</div>
    <p>✔ Provide Affiliation to Institutions, Schools & Training Centres</p>
    <p>✔ Conduct Online & Offline Skill Examinations</p>
    <p>✔ Issue National Skill Certificates</p>
    <p>✔ Register Passed Candidates as Professionals</p>
    <p>✔ Provide Verification Services for Employers</p>
    <p>✔ Develop Courses, Curriculum & Training Materials</p>
    <p>✔ Support Students & Institutions with Digital Learning Tools</p>

    <div class="heading">Professional Candidate Registry</div>
    <p>
        All students who successfully complete their course and pass the assessment examinations 
        are registered under the IIBSE Professional Registry, allowing them to work anywhere in India 
        and abroad. Employers can verify their records online through the official website.
    </p>

</section>

